{% macro tournament_modal() -%}
  <div class="modal fade"
       id="tournament-modal"
       tabindex="-1"
       role="dialog"
       aria-hidden="true">
	   <div class="modal-dialog">
		 <div class="modal-content">
		   <div class="modal-header">
			 <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span><span class="sr-only">Close</span></button>
			 <h4 class="modal-title">Great Chicago Fire Elimination Rules</h4>
		   </div>
		   <div class="modal-body">
			 <div class="center-block">
			   <img src="/static/img/gcf-logo.png"
					class="img-responsive center-block"/>

			   <p>
				 Mockers will compete as a school, instead of as
				 independent teams. There will be sixteen schools at the
				 tournament; each school will have two teams. First
				 round, each school will be paired with another
				 school. For example, if School 1 was paired with School
				 2, each of School 1â€™s teams (1A and 1B) would the
				 corresponding team from School 2 (2A and 2B,
				 respectively). For each pairing of schools, there are
				 two trials, each with three ballots, for a total of six
				 ballots (1A v.1B & 2A v. 2B, three ballots each). From
				 these six ballots, one of the schools is determined the
				 winner of the pairing, and the other school is
				 eliminated, and moves on to the next round where they
				 compete against another school that won in the first
				 round, until only two schools are left in the
				 bracket.
			   </p>

				 <p>
				   When a school loses a round, they drop into a
				   normal tournament with weighted pairings, like a
				   standard AMTA style tournament, so every team will
				   play a full eight rounds. The champion of the
				   regular tournament will be awarded 3rd place.
				 </p>

		   </div>
		 </div><!-- /.modal-content -->
	   </div><!-- /.modal-dialog -->
  </div><!-- /.modal -->

{% endmacro %}


{% macro tournament() -%}
  <section id="fire" class="intro">
	<div class="slogan" id="gcf">
	  <h1>The Great Chicago Fire</h1>
	  <h2> Invitational Tournament </h2>
	  {# <a href="#about" class="btn btn-skin scroll">Learn more</a> #}
	  {# <img src="/static/img/gcf-transparent.png" alt="" class="img-responsive"/> #}
	  {# <img src="/static/img/seal.png" alt="" class="img-responsive"/> #}
	</div>
	{# {{ tournament_banner() }} #}
  </section>
  <section id="fire-info" class="home-section text-center bg-gray">
	<div class="heading-about marginbot-50">
	  <div class="container">
		<div class="row">
		  <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
			<div class="section-heading">
			  <p>The <a href="https://www.facebook.com/greatchicagofireinvitational?fref=ts">Great Chicago Fire</a> is the University's
			  invitational mock trial tournament. Congratulations to the winner of the inaugural competition--The Ohio State University! The second annual Great Chicago Fire invitational will
			  be held from January 16th and January 17th, 2016 at the
			  <a href="//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Everett_McKinley_Dirksen_United_States_Courthouse">
			  Dirksen Federal Courthouse </a> in Downtown
			  Chicago. Unlike most mock trial tournaments, the Great
			  Chicago Fire will feature
				<a data-toggle="modal" href="#" data-target="#tournament-modal">
				  bracket style elimination
				</a>.
			  </p>
			  <p>
				We will be sending out invitations starting in the
				summer of 2015. To learn more, please
				contact <a href="mailto:2f9but0j">the tournament
				committee.</a>
			  </p>
			</div>
		  </div>
		</div>
	  </div>
	</div>
  </section>


{% endmacro %}



